added.title: The Loophole
added.description: Gumball and Darwin give Bobert specific instructions to ensure he acts in a safe and responsible manner. When Bobert starts applying his robot logic to their rules, they soon realize they're going to have to be much clearer. Or he will end up destroying them all.

added.title: The Night
added.description: As night falls in Elmore, the Moon takes us on a tour through the various dreams and nightmares of the town's slumbering inhabitants. Each character's dream shows us their innermost desires, their greatest fears or just how plain weird they are.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Gumball and Darwin seek the answer to the biggest question of all: what is the meaning of life? They need to understand the point of their lives, so resolve to seek advice from everyone in Elmore. They ask people, animals and even planets but their answer comes from an unexpected source.

added.title: The Phone
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin get their first cell phone, they foolishly give out their number to super-intense Ocho.

added.title: The Car
added.description: Gumball and Darwin accidentally destroy Mr Robinson's new car...or do they?

added.title: Aquarium for a Dream
added.description: Gwen tries to convince Chef to tell the class the truth about their pet goldfish.

added.title: Cuttin' Corners
added.description: Duncan, Leshawna and Jude all want corner pieces of Izzy's Birthday Cake… But are they prepared to go to any length to get one?

added.title: Sharing Is Caring
added.description: Courtney refuses to share her valuable collectors item toy with her classmates.

added.title: Cone in 60 Seconds
added.description: After Owen gets ripped off at the ice cream truck, the kids unite to right that wrong.

added.title: The Bad Guy Busters
added.description: Izzy wants to play a superhero game and is willing to do whatever it takes to get the others to see it through.

added.title: That's a Wrap
added.description: Duncan goes on a mission to scare Courtney during a field trip to the museum.

added.title: Tiger Fail
added.description: Gwen refuses to be pressured into choosing an ice cream flavor that she does not want.

added.title: The Good Lars
added.description: Steven, Lars and Sadie get invited to a party with the Cool Kids.

added.title: Beach City Drift
added.description: Steven and Connie get into a high-speed car race with their biggest foe.

added.title: Angel Face
added.description: BMO ropes his friends into a live action cowboy role-playing adventure!

added.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
added.description: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

added.title: Root Beer Guy
added.description: Root Beer Guy works a boring job during the day and tries to write mystery stories at night. But his life is about to change when he witnesses Finn and Jake kidnapping Princess Bubblegum! There's only one problem: no one believes Root Beer Guy.

added.title: Goliad
added.description: Princess Bubblegum, concerned over her mortality, reveals her designated successor to Finn & Jake - but he still has a lot to learn.

added.title: The New Frontier
added.description: When Jake has a dream that predicts when his last days are, Finn intervenes when the events of the dream start to actually happen.

added.title: Busted Cart
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby bust up the cart while doing stunts and have to figure out a way to fix it.

added.title: Access Denied
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to go to Margaret's birthday party at an exclusive club.

added.title: Trucker Hall of Fame
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Muscle Man get to the Big Rig Museum to spread his dad's hat's ashes.

added.title: Diary
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to fix a lock on Margaret's diary before she gets back from a weekend trip.

added.title: Prankless
added.description: The guys want to win a prank war with a rival park.

added.title: La Super Increible Aventura en Balsa
added.description: Unikitty y Hawkodile están "perdidos en el mar," varados en una balsa juntos. Hawkodile ve esto como una oportunidad para mostrarle a Unikitty que está preparado para cualquier cosa con sus habilidades de experto en supervivencia, pero para su sorpresa, todos sus planes fracasan, mientras que la tonta postura de Unikitty de "todo saldrá bien, vamos a divertirnos" está funcionando de una manera genial. ¿Será Hawkodile capaz de soltar su exceso de preparación para salvarlos a ambos, o acaso la diversión caprichosa de Unikitty será su perdición?

added.title: Visita Monstruosa
added.description: Los monstruos se ponen nerviosos cuando su Dios monstruo llega de visita.

added.title: Pantalones Movedizos del Tiempo
added.description: Oscar y Erizo se enteran de la existencia de unas arenas movedizas que les permiten viajar en el tiempo.

added.title: El Popular Banana Split
added.description: Erizo y Max descubren una escuela diminuta cuando, por accidente, un experimento científico los encoge.

added.title: Es mi Fiesta
added.description: Oscar y Erizo planean una fiesta de cumpleaños sorpresa para Susie.

added.title: Problemas Lunares
added.description: La Luna se entristece cuando Oscar pierde su brazalete de la amistad.

added.title: Sabro Atraco
added.description: Richard preparó uno de los postres más sabrosos de todos los tiempos, pero lo cerró con llave hasta que los amigos terminen su cena aburrida. Esto no va a seguir así. Para organizar un atraco, Unikitty organiza a sus amigos como un comité de expertos para entrar, salir y comer ese sabroso bocadillo sin que Richard lo sepa. Pero este atraco tiene un traspié. ¿Podrán los amigos llevarse el pastel?

removed.title: Nightmare Hospital
removed.description: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.

removed.title: Hit the Diamond
removed.description: Steven and the Gems play an old fashioned game of baseball.

removed.title: Room for Ruby
removed.description: Steven's Gem family continues to grow.

removed.title: Guardians of Sunshine
removed.description: Finn and Jake go into BMO to defeat an evil Big Boss.

removed.title: The Music Hole
removed.description: While judging the hugest Battle of the Bands in the history of Ooo, Finn hears a mysterious new song.

removed.title: Summer Showers
removed.description: Jake's daughter Viola is up for a role in a play by a hot new director, Lumpy Space Princess.

removed.title: What Have You Done?
removed.description: Finn and Jake befriend the Ice King in an attempt to save the ice cream people.

removed.title: Evergreen
removed.description: In a distant age, the wizard Evergreen quests to save the world.

removed.title: Butt Dial
removed.description: Mordecai pocket dials an embarrassing message on Margaret's phone.

removed.title: Replaced
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby find out that Benson is going to replace them and have to figure out a way to stop it.

removed.title: Fists of Justice
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to do all of Skips' duties for the day.

removed.title: Big Winner
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby give Muscle Man a lottery ticket for his birthday.
